Gauteng Premier David Makhura has announced the provincial cabinet. Gauteng Government spokesperson, Thabo Masebe with the latest. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura has announced his ten-member cabinet. There are six new faces in Gauteng’s executive council. Makhura’s deputy in the ANC, Panyaza Lesufi has been moved from Education to Finance and e-Government. Nomantu Nkomo-Ralehoko has replaced Lesufi as the head of the Education portfolio. The rest of Makhura’s cabinet comprises of the following; The new MECs will be sworn in on Thursday at Emoyeni Conference Centre.